article.description: Raasean Davis had 19 points as North Carolina Central narrowly beat North Carolina A&T 65-63 in the Mid-Eastern Conference tourney semifinals on Friday night.
article.headline: Davis scores 19 to lift NC Central past NC A&T 65-63
article.linkText: Davis scores 19 to lift NC Central past NC A&T 65-63
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Raasean Davis had 19 points as North Carolina Central narrowly beat North Carolina A&T 65-63 in the Mid-Eastern Conference tourney semifinals on Friday night. Randy Miller, Jr. had 17 points for NC Central (17-15). Zacarry Douglas added eight rebounds. Kameron Langley had 14 points and 10 assists for the Aggies (19-13). Terry Harris added 14 points. Ibrahim Sylla had 10 points. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
